article.description: — Jeremiah Pope had 14 points off the bench to carry Rider to a 63-53 win over Delaware State on Sunday.
article.headline: Pope scores 14 to lead Rider past Delaware St. 63-53
article.linkText: Pope scores 14 to lead Rider past Delaware St. 63-53
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- — Jeremiah Pope had 14 points off the bench to carry Rider to a 63-53 win over Delaware State on Sunday. Dwight Murray Jr. had 13 points for Rider (2-1). Dimencio Vaughn added 12 points. Ajiri Ogemuno-Johnson had 10 points and 12 rebounds. Myles Carter had 17 points and eight rebounds for the Hornets (1-2). Fahim Jenneto added 13 points. Dominik Fragala had 10 points. Chris Sodom had a career-high 15 rebounds plus 6 points and five blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25------ Information from: Automated Insights, http://automatedinsights.com/ ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
